      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Works of art, traditionally from the 18th and 19th century in Great Britain, that depict "country pursuits" such as game hunting, fishing, dog racing, horse racing, and pugilism. The genre is sometimes expanded to works of art that depict any kind of amateur or professional sport.</Note_Text>
